  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthen national policies and international development agendas through integration of evidence-based analysis on population dynamics and their links to sustainable development, sexual and reproductive health and reprooductive rights, HIV and gender</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To influence international and national policy makers into adopting policies that benefit older people through ensuring solid evidence and trends on ageing is made available to policy-makers. The project will provide an informed compilation of new work focusing on re-conceptualizing the &quot;costs&quot; of ageing from one narrowly defined by financing and expenditure to one of investment and long-term planning in the areas of social protection, health and social care, urban environments and infrastructure. The work focuses on the overall state of issues relating to investments in policies addressing the economic issues of global ageing, looking particularly at the situation of low and medium income countries and their contextual challenges</narrative>
  </description>
